.TH PROTON-DRIVE 1 "2026-06-06" "0.1.0" "Proton Drive (Unofficial)"
.SH NAME
proton-drive \- Unofficial Proton Drive command-line client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B proton-drive
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This is an unofficial, community-developed client for Proton Drive. It is not
affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Proton AG. Proton Drive is a
trademark of Proton AG.
.PP
Proton Drive is an end-to-end encrypted cloud storage service.
.B proton-drive
provides a command-line interface to manage your Proton Drive account
and synchronize files.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B auth login
Log in to your Proton account.
.TP
.B auth logout
Log out and revoke the current session.
.TP
.B auth status
Show the current authentication status.
.TP
.B ls [OPTIONS] [PATH]
List files and folders.
\fB--recursive\fR, \fB-r\fR  List recursively.
\fB--decrypt\fR, \fB-d\fR   Decrypt file names (prompts for password).
.TP
.B status
Show sync status (requires protond to be running).
.TP
.B sync
Sync the local drive with the remote (requires protond).
.TP
.B resolve [OPTIONS] [PATH]
List or resolve conflicts.
\fB--strategy\fR \fIstrategy\fR  Resolution strategy: local, remote, rename_local.
.TP
.B mkdir NAME
Create a remote folder.
\fB--share-id\fR \fIid\fR        Parent share ID.
\fB--parent-link-id\fR \fIid\fR  Parent folder link ID.
\fB--password\fR \fIpw\fR        Decryption password.
.TP
.B rename --share-id ID --link-id ID --new-name NAME
Rename a remote file or folder.
\fB--password\fR \fIpw\fR        Decryption password.
.TP
.B rm --share-id ID --link-id ID
Delete a remote file or folder.
.TP
.B transfer [CONFIG]
Show or configure the transfer schedule.
CONFIG is a JSON object with a "windows" array of time windows.
Each window has optional "days" (e.g. ["Mon","Tue"]) and
required "start" and "end" times in HH:MM format.
.TP
.B pause
Pause all background transfers and sync.
.TP
.B resume
Resume background transfers and sync.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/proton-drive/
Local database and configuration.
.TP
.I ~/Proton Drive/
Local synchronized directory.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/agusti-grau/proton-drive-client/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR protond (1)
